text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Ohio was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Incumbent President Donald Trump and his running mate Vice President Mike Pence had won 18 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:21st century in Ohio
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Ohio
